article_title: Is Obamacare Squeezing The Middle Class?

article_metadata.author: John C. Goodman

og.description: Here is something few pundits predicted. Poor, long-uninsured patients are getting Medicaid through Obamacare and finally going to the doctor’s office for care. But middle-class patients are increasingly staying away. Take Praveen Arla, who helps his father run a family practice in Hillview, Kentucky. The Arlas' patient load used to be 45% [...]
